{
  "name": "stride-stroller-community-app",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "A community walking and stroller group tracker built with a single HTML file and Firebase.",
  "main": "public/index.html",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "firebase serve --only hosting",
    "deploy": "firebase deploy --only hosting"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "firebase-tools": "^13.0.0"
  }
}


#### D. `firebase.json` (Hosting Configuration)

This directs Firebase to serve files from the `public` folder and to treat `index.html` as the main app page.

```json
{
  "hosting": {
    "public": "public",
    "ignore": [
      "firebase.json",
      "**/.*",
      "**/node_modules/**"
    ],
    "rewrites": [
      {
        "source": "**",
        "destination": "/index.html"
      }
    ]
  }
}


#### E. `public/manifest.json` (PWA Configuration)

This enables the user to "Add to Home Screen" and defines the icon's look when installed.

```json
{
  "name": "Stride & Stroller Community",
  "short_name": "StrideStroller",
  "description": "Organize and find local walking and stroller groups.",
  "start_url": "/index.html",
  "display": "standalone",
  "background_color": "#E8F5E9",
  "theme_color": "#4CAF50",
  "icons": [
    {
      "src": "/assets/icons/icon-192x192.png",
      "sizes": "192x192",
      "type": "image/png"
    },
    {
      "src": "/assets/icons/icon-512x512.png",
      "sizes": "512x512",
      "type": "image/png"
    }
  ]
}


#### F. `public/404.html` (Error Page)

A simple page to catch broken links.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 - Page Not Found</title>
</head>
<body style="font-family: sans-serif; text-align: center; padding: 50px;">
    <h1>404</h1>
    <p>Oops! We couldn't find that walk. The page you're looking for doesn't exist.</p>
    <p><a href="/">Go to the homepage</a></p>
</body>
</html>
